Class AbstractStream

    ByteStream, CSVStream, FixedFieldStream, MessageStream, NativeStream, PrintStream, PropertiesStream, XMLStream, XMLXStream, ZipStream

    public abstract class AbstractStream
extends PropertyAccessMap
implements PhysicalIO, Cloneable
    Provides utility functionality for sub-classes which implement the PhysicalIO interface for I/O to streams.

      • makeStreams

        protected final boolean makeStreams(Process p,
                                    Any toOpen,
                                    IntI mode)
                             throws AnyException
        Make streams to the underlying source represented by the URL. Where supported, streams will be created according to the supplied mode.

        The streams created only make the connection to the underlying source/sink and are not characterised with any particular format, such as native serialised form or text line-based. That function is performed by derived implementations of acceptStreams, which can be called after this method has executed successfully.

        If the supplied URL, toOpen, is relative then it is based on the file:// protocol, assuming the user's current working directory.

        Throws:
        AnyException
